        <div class="project-paragraph">
            My undergraduate capstone studio brief was for a community health centre in Melbourne. I chose to rewrite this brief and set the centre in the year 2119 - challenging the ideas of â€˜communityâ€™ and â€˜health careâ€™ in their current forms and expressions in the build environment. 
            <br /><br />
            â€‹
            
            The Mothership is a facility is compatible with the lifestyle of the 22nd century client. Users are able to sync their personal domains with a healthcare typology. Here, the forefronts of technology and advancements in healthcare are made available to the community. A visit to the Mothership is a mere extension of the digital world and facet of everyday life.
            <br /><br />
            â€‹
            
            â€‹This proposal is a response to future issues such as our growing population and increased demand on resources, where clients expect robotic efficiency but yearn for human nurture; <span class="para-emphasis">a Mothership solution.</span>
